CSS - ?
	Is a Styling Lang used for websites,
	Cascading style sheets.
	->how html displayed on screen .
	->layouts of websites.
	->designs.

	Styles:
		property:value.
		color:red;

	3 ways to use css in html.
		-> div ,span,input

	1] inline css - OK.
		Style attribute.
		<div class="" width="" style="" ></div>

	2] Internal CSS:
		Style Tag
		<style>
			/* head tag -> body is ok.*/

			selector{
				color:red;
				/*css properties.*/
				background-color: black;
			}

			ex 
				h1{
					color:red;
				}

		</style>
		/*Selectors 
				used to target an element/tag.
		*/	

	CSS Apply -> Tags
		Target/Select .

	Sytax:
		<h2 style="color:red;">
		</h2>

	#Border ?
		/*shorthand property*/
		border : borderWidth borderStyle borderColor;
		ex border:2px solid red;

		/*Separate properties.*/
		border-width:5px;
		border-style:solid;
		border-color:red;

		border-top-style:dotted;
		border-left-style:solid;
		border-bottom-style:groove;
		border-right-style:dashed;

		border-top-style:solid;
		border-top-width:5px;
		border-top-color:green;

		/*shorthand*/
		border-top:5px solid green;

		border-left:5px solid green;
		border-right:5px solid green;
		border-bottom:5px solid green;

		border-radius -< used to add rounded borders to elements.
		border-radius:5px;

Font :
		font-size: 50px;
			font-weight: bolder;
			font-family: monospace , cursive;
			font-style: italic;
			font-variant: small-caps ;

			/*shorthand property*/
			font:italic small-caps bolder 50px cursive;


The CSS height and width properties are used to set the height and width of an element.
		
	 height: 200px;
  	 width: 50%;

	auto - This is default. The browser calculates the height and width
	
	length - Defines the height/width in px, cm etc.

	% - Defines the height/width in percent of the containing block

	initial - Sets the height/width to its default value

	inherit - The height/width will be inherited from its parent value

The CSS max-width property is used to set the maximum width of an element.
The CSS min-width property is used to set the minimum width of an element.


